## What to Test at Each Layer

### Unit Tests (70% of suite)
- Pure business logic with zero I/O
- Memory compressor: input Markdown → correct matrix schema and row count
- Circuit breaker state transitions: closed → open → half_open → closed
- Retry logic: correct attempt count, correct backoff timing
- Skill tool extraction: valid `index.ts` → correct `ToolDefinition` list
- Error classifier: exception type → correct `error_class` tag
- `SecretMasker`: fields with "token", "key", "password" → `***REDACTED***`

### Integration Tests (25% of suite)
- Use real PostgreSQL (test DB, transactional rollback)
- Mock the LLM gateway
- API endpoint tests: correct status codes, response shapes, auth enforcement
- Skill executor: timeout enforcement, exception handling, health_check bypass
- Memory retrieval: episodic similarity search returns ranked results
- Scheduler: job registration and `list_jobs()` accuracy

### E2E Tests (5% of suite, Playwright)
- Chat flow: type message → send → receive streamed response
- Provider status visible on health dashboard
- Error banner appears when API returns 503
- SSE reconnects after simulated connection drop

