## What Is NOT Worth Testing

| Item | Reason |
|---|---|
| That APScheduler fires at the right time | Test job *logic*, not APScheduler's accuracy |
| That watchdog delivers inotify events | Test the *handler*, not OS event delivery |
| That nginx proxies correctly | Infrastructure concern, not unit-testable |
| That Docker containers start | Integration concern for CI, not unit tests |
| LLM response quality in unit tests | Non-deterministic — use `@pytest.mark.llm_eval` |
| Pydantic field validation | Pydantic is already tested; test your schema definition |

---

## Test Commands

```bash
make test          # Fast suite: unit + integration, mocked LLM (~30–60s)
make test-eval     # LLM quality tests: real providers (slow, costs tokens)
make test-e2e      # Playwright (requires make dev running)
make test-chaos    # Circuit breaker + fallback stress tests
make test-cov      # Coverage report → htmlcov/index.html
```

**Target:** `make test` completes in under 60 seconds.
If it takes longer, investigate and fix — slow tests don't get run.

